# CSS & Styling Standards

## BEM Methodology
All CSS must follow the **BEM (Block Element Modifier)** pattern:

```css
/* ✅ Good: BEM Pattern */
.index {
  /* Block styles */
}

.index__content {
  /* Element styles */
}

.index__content--highlighted {
  /* Modifier styles */
}

/* ❌ Bad: Non-BEM patterns */
.container .header .title {
  /* Avoid nested selectors */
}
```

## CSS Module Patterns
- Use CSS modules for component-specific styles
- Follow the naming convention: `[component].module.css`
- Export class names as camelCase from CSS modules

## Styling Hierarchy
1. **Shopify Polaris**: Use built-in Polaris components and design tokens
2. **Custom Components**: Use CSS modules with BEM methodology
3. **Global Styles**: Minimal global styles, prefer component-scoped styles

## Responsive Design
- Use mobile-first approach
- Implement proper breakpoints
- Test on various screen sizes

## Performance Considerations
- Minimize CSS bundle size
- Use efficient selectors
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)
- Use CSS custom properties for theming

## Example Implementation
```css
/* styles.module.css */
.projectCard {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 1rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background-color: var(--p-color-bg-surface);
}

.projectCard__header {
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.projectCard__title {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.projectCard__title--featured {
  color: var(--p-color-text-brand);
}

.projectCard__content {
  flex: 1;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .projectCard {
    padding: 0.75rem;
  }
}
```